  "text": "Using cellular data links for UAVs at the same time with serving the ground users is the main focus of [CITATION_1] . Comprehensive analysis of current and next-generation cellular networks are studied. The current traditional topology is based on single user mode, which means one user is served per frequency-time resource at each time, whereas in next generation, multi-user massive MIMO (multiple input multiple output) BSs are available. The latter means at each time, multiple users will be served per frequency-time resource.",
